==Old English==
===Etymology===
West Germanic ''*sterro'', from Germanic ''*stirnaz'', from Indo-European ''*h₂ster-''.

''Germanic cognates:'' Old Frisian [[stera|stēra]], Old Saxon [[sterro]] (Dutch [[ster]]), Old High German [[sterro]]; Old High German [[sterno]] (German [[Stern]]), Old Norse [[stjarna]] (Swedish [[stjärna]]), Gothic [[𐍃𐍄𐌰𐌹𐍂𐌽𐍉]].

''Indo-European cognates:'' Greek [[ἀστήρ]], Latin [[stella|stēlla]], Breton [[sterenn]], Tocharian A ''śre''

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'steoɹɹa/

===Noun===
